<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}-{3}{y}=-{46}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{6}{x}-{2}{y}=-{52}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{8},{2}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}+-{3}{y}=-{46}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}=-{46}-{\left(-{3}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{46}-{\left(-{3}{y}\right)}}}{{5}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{\left(\frac{{-{46}-{\left(-{3}{y}\right)}}}{{5}}\right)}+-{2}{y}=-{52}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{6}}{{5}}\cdot{\left(-{46}\right)}-\frac{{6}}{{5}}{\left(-{3}\right)}{y}+-{2}{y}=-{52}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{55.2}-{\left({3.6}\right)}{y}+-{2}{y}=-{52}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3.6}{y}+{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}=-{52}--{55.2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3.6}{y}+{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}={3.2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({3.6}+{\left(-{2}\right)}\right)}{y}={3.2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1.6}{y}={3.2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{3.2}}{{1.6}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={2}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}+-{3}{\left({2}\right)}=-{46}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}+{\left(-{6}\right)}=-{46}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}=-{46}-{\left(-{6}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}=-{40}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{40}}{{5}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{8}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{8},{2}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

